256
00:14:26,866 --> 00:14:27,867
Wow.

257
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:31,120
She's right.

258
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:34,040
- They died young.
- Ah…

259
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:35,291
-Yes.
-My word.

260
00:14:35,374 --> 00:14:38,795
- They all died before turning 50.
- His father's brothers.

261
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:40,338
I've never seen a shaman so accurate.

262
00:14:40,421 --> 00:14:41,798
ALL BUT ONE OF FATHER'S BROTHERS
DIED BEFORE 50

263
00:14:41,881 --> 00:14:43,674
Wow.

264
00:14:43,758 --> 00:14:48,221
It's true that the men
in my family tend to die young.

265
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:51,224
My family name is Oh,

266
00:14:51,307 --> 00:14:54,393
and our clan has been faced
with a lot of retribution and penalties.

267
00:14:54,477 --> 00:14:56,562
The men don't live long.

268
00:14:56,646 --> 00:15:00,066
She got my family history right.

269
00:15:00,149 --> 00:15:02,318
It was almost frightening, to be honest.

270
00:15:02,985 --> 00:15:04,403
She saw right through me.

271
00:15:05,238 --> 00:15:08,741
- How does she know all that?
- It's like she read this book.

272
00:15:08,825 --> 00:15:10,576
- I can't keep up.
- No.

273
00:15:11,285 --> 00:15:14,413
Your father's brothers
didn't live that long?

274
00:15:14,497 --> 00:15:17,875
His family was cursed
because of issues with the graveyard.

275
00:15:17,959 --> 00:15:21,963
They've lost family members
3 years in a row.

276
00:15:22,046 --> 00:15:25,800
My mother tried many rites
because of that,

277
00:15:25,883 --> 00:15:27,635
but it didn't help.

278
00:15:28,970 --> 00:15:31,305
The people
in your father's family.

279
00:15:31,389 --> 00:15:32,932
How old were they

280
00:15:33,015 --> 00:15:36,310
when they passed?

281
00:15:36,394 --> 00:15:37,687
From what I remember,

282
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:40,148
his youngest brother died in his 20s.

283
00:15:40,231 --> 00:15:43,192
Oh, dear. He died way too young.

284
00:15:44,193 --> 00:15:47,071
And the brother
right above my father

285
00:15:47,155 --> 00:15:49,323
passed in his late 40s.

286
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:53,494
- He died young.
- They all died young.

287
00:15:54,662 --> 00:15:56,998
My concern is…

288
00:15:57,373 --> 00:15:59,667
After I became a shaman,

289
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:02,378
which was in 2022,

290
00:16:02,461 --> 00:16:05,173
from then until 2023,

291
00:16:05,256 --> 00:16:07,341
7 of my friends died in that 1 year.

292
00:16:11,971 --> 00:16:13,222
That must've been tough.

293
00:16:13,848 --> 00:16:15,558
- His friends?
- Seven of them.

294
00:16:16,517 --> 00:16:19,562
The truth is, when the death curse hit,

295
00:16:19,645 --> 00:16:23,274
I actually knew beforehand
that my friends would die.

296
00:16:24,317 --> 00:16:25,484
- Gosh.
- Because

297
00:16:25,568 --> 00:16:29,238
in the last week of October 2022,

298
00:16:29,322 --> 00:16:32,783
there was a terrible incident in Itaewon.

299
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:34,744
- The incident in Itaewon.
- Yes.

300
00:16:34,827 --> 00:16:37,246
Three of my friends died there.

301
00:16:37,330 --> 00:16:38,789
Oh, dear.

302
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:45,588
I was praying on Mount Worak that day,

303
00:16:45,671 --> 00:16:49,175
and my friends told me
to come to Itaewon when I was done.

304
00:16:49,258 --> 00:16:53,512
I was going to go, but my Granny spirit
screamed, "Don't go!"

305
00:16:53,596 --> 00:16:55,014
So, I didn't go.

306
00:16:56,557 --> 00:16:57,642
This is crazy.

307
00:17:02,230 --> 00:17:04,732
So I went back to my shrine after praying,

308
00:17:04,815 --> 00:17:07,360
and I saw my 3 friends standing

309
00:17:07,443 --> 00:17:09,362
by the door with broken bodies.

310
00:17:12,198 --> 00:17:13,199
Oh, my word.

311
00:17:15,785 --> 00:17:16,786
I'm scared.

312
00:17:18,371 --> 00:17:21,415
As soon as I entered the shrine,
my Grandpa spirit told me

313
00:17:21,499 --> 00:17:23,501
to put a lid over the water offering bowl,

314
00:17:23,584 --> 00:17:26,128
blow out the candles,
smoke myself with incense,

315
00:17:26,212 --> 00:17:27,672
and keep the door closed.

316
00:17:28,172 --> 00:17:31,676
That night, I made a straw rope

317
00:17:31,759 --> 00:17:33,803
and hung it across the door.

318
00:17:33,886 --> 00:17:36,556
My Grandpa spirit said
even though he feels bad to say it,

319
00:17:36,639 --> 00:17:39,809
even a friend is just a ghost
once they're dead.

320
00:17:42,937 --> 00:17:44,272
That's true.

321
00:17:44,355 --> 00:17:46,315
- Oh.
- If you don't help

322
00:17:46,399 --> 00:17:48,359
a ghost move on,

323
00:17:49,569 --> 00:17:50,945
they keep coming back.

324
00:17:51,028 --> 00:17:52,780
- Do they really?
- Yes.

325
00:17:52,863 --> 00:17:54,824
Oh, my neck.

326
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:59,662
I untangled a goppae
so that they'd move on,

327
00:18:00,329 --> 00:18:02,415
and I kept praying for them,

328
00:18:02,498 --> 00:18:05,042
but there was a limit to what I could do.

329
00:18:05,126 --> 00:18:06,335
Hmm.

330
00:18:06,419 --> 00:18:08,170
I know many of my close relatives

331
00:18:08,254 --> 00:18:11,257
and friends are meant to die young.

332
00:18:14,468 --> 00:18:17,346
I'd appreciate it if you could tell me

333
00:18:17,430 --> 00:18:19,432
if this is going to keep happening.

334
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:25,771
My heart breaks for him.

335
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:28,316
Well…

336
00:18:28,399 --> 00:18:31,068
I haven't been a shaman for long, but…

337
00:18:31,152 --> 00:18:33,321
I grew up without parents,

338
00:18:33,404 --> 00:18:36,324
and my younger brother was all I had.

339
00:18:36,407 --> 00:18:37,992
But he died when I was

340
00:18:38,075 --> 00:18:39,619
in my last year of high school,

341
00:18:39,702 --> 00:18:41,412
and that's when
my shamanic illness worsened,

342
00:18:41,495 --> 00:18:43,623
and I struggled
to compete in sports in university.

343
00:18:44,915 --> 00:18:46,250
Oh, dear.

344
00:18:46,334 --> 00:18:47,710
They're so similar.

345
00:18:48,336 --> 00:18:50,338
We keep on facing death.

346
00:18:50,421 --> 00:18:53,924
That seems to be the fate of a shaman.

347
00:18:54,008 --> 00:18:55,384
So in a way,

348
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:58,387
whether it be
a close family member or a friend,

349
00:18:58,471 --> 00:19:00,556
you're likely to lose people,

350
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:02,433
and it runs in the family.

351
00:19:02,516 --> 00:19:05,478
You must pray and cleanse
the malicious energy.

352
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:10,733
That's a scary thing to hear.

353
00:19:11,275 --> 00:19:12,693
She's saying more people will die.

354
00:19:20,660 --> 00:19:22,328
She's really good.

355
00:19:22,411 --> 00:19:23,704
That was one heck of a reading.

356
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:27,458
- They're both so very good.
- I know.

357
00:19:29,335 --> 00:19:31,504
She got a lot of things right.

358
00:19:31,587 --> 00:19:34,423
The most shocking was that she got
that his dad's brothers died young.

359
00:19:34,507 --> 00:19:35,508
Right.

360
00:19:36,008 --> 00:19:37,510
This is how they do it.

361
00:19:37,593 --> 00:19:39,929
-They speak as if they see it happening.
-Exactly.

362
00:19:40,012 --> 00:19:41,430
It's as if they see it.

363
00:19:41,514 --> 00:19:43,432
It's so freaky.

364
00:19:44,141 --> 00:19:46,268
Lady Wish spoke so quickly

365
00:19:46,352 --> 00:19:49,647
