before she told me.

1042
00:58:22,791 --> 00:58:24,376
Goodness.

1043
00:58:27,671 --> 00:58:28,797
That's pretty similar.

1044
00:58:36,763 --> 00:58:39,266
This is so…

1045
00:58:39,349 --> 00:58:42,018
I guess he's saying
you should let her find out herself.

1046
00:58:42,102 --> 00:58:43,812
You don't need to tell her.

1047
00:58:46,440 --> 00:58:47,983
It must've been tough for your mom.

1048
00:58:54,239 --> 00:58:57,033
You said you figured out
your mother's a shaman

1049
00:58:57,117 --> 00:58:58,869
even though nobody told you.

1050
00:58:58,952 --> 00:59:00,287
How did you know?

1051
00:59:00,746 --> 00:59:03,582
At first, she lied to me and said

1052
00:59:03,665 --> 00:59:06,042
she was working at a fruit store.

1053
00:59:06,126 --> 00:59:09,004
And she'd always come home
with some fruit.

1054
00:59:10,046 --> 00:59:12,132
Leftover fruit from the rites.

1055
00:59:12,215 --> 00:59:14,551
- Yes, there's lots of them.
- A lot of leftovers.

1056
00:59:15,218 --> 00:59:17,763
Sometimes she'd say,
"I'll bring home some pork."

1057
00:59:17,846 --> 00:59:18,889
It was always vacuum-packed,

1058
00:59:18,972 --> 00:59:21,141
though I didn't know what that meant.

1059
00:59:21,224 --> 00:59:23,185
They vacuum-pack it after a rite.

1060
00:59:25,061 --> 00:59:26,396
After using a pig in the rite.

1061
00:59:26,480 --> 00:59:28,315
Vacuum-packed meat. So relatable.

1062
00:59:29,357 --> 00:59:32,486
One day, I looked at my mom and said,

1063
00:59:33,862 --> 00:59:36,323
"I want to meet Grandpa and Grandma."

1064
00:59:36,406 --> 00:59:38,658
I asked her to take me with her.

1065
00:59:40,035 --> 00:59:42,370
My mom burst into tears when I said that.

1066
00:59:42,996 --> 00:59:45,248
I went to my mom's shrine,

1067
00:59:45,332 --> 00:59:48,460
saw the deities,
and figured out who was who

1068
00:59:48,543 --> 00:59:50,587
all on my own.

1069
00:59:51,338 --> 00:59:52,756
Whoa.

1070
01:00:00,138 --> 01:00:04,017
Seulbi, he said your daughter
would find out on her own.

1071
01:00:04,100 --> 01:00:07,395
Do you also think your daughter's clever?

1072
01:00:12,025 --> 01:00:13,693
She's so…

1073
01:00:15,570 --> 01:00:16,905
She's a dummy.

1074
01:00:22,828 --> 01:00:24,371
Looks like talking about her child

1075
01:00:25,705 --> 01:00:26,957
is making her emotional.

1076
01:00:27,040 --> 01:00:29,709
Your heart breaks
whenever you talk about your child.

1077
01:00:31,753 --> 01:00:34,631
It's true that she walks
on eggshells around people,

1078
01:00:35,215 --> 01:00:36,758
and she can't read yet.

1079
01:00:40,637 --> 01:00:42,889
I wonder if it's because
I don't spend enough time with her.

1080
01:00:45,600 --> 01:00:46,726
Also…

1081
01:00:47,561 --> 01:00:50,063
I would do absolutely anything

1082
01:00:50,146 --> 01:00:52,399
if what he said would just come true.

1083
01:00:54,943 --> 01:00:55,986
I really…

1084
01:00:56,695 --> 01:00:59,030
- May I say something?
- Yes.

1085
01:01:00,991 --> 01:01:03,118
I still can't memorize the times tables.

1086
01:01:04,119 --> 01:01:05,662
What?

1087
01:01:05,745 --> 01:01:07,080
Huh?

1088
01:01:12,711 --> 01:01:14,796
Has it ever caused you any trouble?

1089
01:01:14,880 --> 01:01:17,215
Calculators are pretty good these days.

1090
01:01:18,383 --> 01:01:21,928
But I'm great at handling money.

1091
01:01:24,556 --> 01:01:26,349
We're good at that. We are.

1092
01:01:27,100 --> 01:01:29,769
Look, my point is,

1093
01:01:29,853 --> 01:01:32,606
even though
I can't memorize the times tables,

1094
01:01:32,689 --> 01:01:35,734
I'm a shaman.
I was always meant to be one.

1095
01:01:35,817 --> 01:01:38,778
My deities gave me the ability
to memorize chants

1096
01:01:38,862 --> 01:01:40,322
or rite proceedings,

1097
01:01:40,405 --> 01:01:43,408
which are more important to me
than the times tables.

1098
01:01:43,909 --> 01:01:45,911
I'm holding on to my fate
till the day I die.

1099
01:01:48,538 --> 01:01:50,874
Will my daughter become a shaman too?

1100
01:01:54,836 --> 01:01:56,671
No.

1101
01:01:56,755 --> 01:01:57,756
That's a relief.

1102
01:02:00,383 --> 01:02:02,469
- She'll be good at something, right?
- Of course.

1103
01:02:02,552 --> 01:02:05,305
It's all about figuring out
what's right for her.

1104
01:02:06,014 --> 01:02:07,474
The deities are fair.

1105
01:02:07,557 --> 01:02:10,060
They give us what we need the most,

1106
01:02:10,143 --> 01:02:11,895
so I think that's actually a good sign.

1107
01:02:11,978 --> 01:02:15,607
That's right. Hyunmoo,
you went to a prestigious university.

1108
01:02:15,690 --> 01:02:17,150
- Yes.
- I only finished high school.

1109
01:02:17,233 --> 01:02:19,486
- But we're both successful.
- That's right.

1110
01:02:19,569 --> 01:02:21,655
Everyone's born with a different talent.

1111
01:02:21,738 --> 01:02:23,031
It has nothing to do with your studies.

1112
01:02:23,114 --> 01:02:24,115
That's right.

1113
01:02:25,533 --> 01:02:27,243
Seulbi,

1114
01:02:27,869 --> 01:02:30,121
you're doing so well right now.

1115
01:02:30,205 --> 01:02:34,167
You want to make sure
your girl never feels small.

1116
01:02:34,918 --> 01:02:36,294
You want to help her stand tall.

1117
01:02:37,212 --> 01:02:40,090
That's why you're working so hard,

1118
01:02:40,173 --> 01:02:41,841
pretending to be fine when you're not.

1119
01:02:41,925 --> 01:02:46,429
Seulbi, you may be soft on the inside
and might be heartbroken,

1120
01:02:46,513 --> 01:02:48,682
but you're a strong mother.

1121
01:02:50,225 --> 01:02:51,309
Right.

1122
01:02:54,062 --> 01:02:56,481
That's what I wanted to hear so badly.

1123
01:02:58,733 --> 01:03:01,152
Young Master Jiseon is so mature.

1124
01:03:01,236 --> 01:03:02,612
He's sweet.

1125
01:03:02,696 --> 01:03:05,031
That's not something
an ordinary 18-year-old can say.

1126
01:03:05,115 --> 01:03:06,241
No.

1127
01:03:09,744 --> 01:03:12,163
Seulbi mentioned

1128
01:03:12,247 --> 01:03:16,835
that you had trouble
getting along with people.

1129
01:03:16,918 --> 01:03:20,171
Wait, you were a Tagada Disco DJ?

1130
01:03:20,255 --> 01:03:21,548
2025, AGED 18
WORKED AS TAGADA DISCO DJ

1131
01:03:21,631 --> 01:03:23,675
You were a Tagada Disco DJ?

1132
01:03:27,053 --> 01:03:30,432
The star of all teenage girls.

1133
01:03:30,515 --> 01:03:33,518
"Let's go, let's go. It's time to go."

1134
01:03:33,601 --> 01:03:36,688
It says here that he blows off stress

1135
01:03:36,771 --> 01:03:39,149
by jumping around on a Tagada.

1136
01:03:40,650 --> 01:03:42,610
Although it's not a jakdu.

1137
01:03:42,694 --> 01:03:45,447
You need to be really outgoing
and extroverted

1138
01:03:45,530 --> 01:03:47,449
to do that job.

1139
01:03:47,532 --> 01:03:50,452
But you still had trouble making friends?

1140
01:03:51,036 --> 01:03:53,079
Okay, so I've been a shaman

1141
01:03:53,163 --> 01:03:55,665
since I was 5 years old.

1142
01:03:55,749 --> 01:03:58,043
I had no time to myself.

1143
01:03:58,126 --> 01:03:59,753
- True.
- I just told fortunes

1144
01:03:59,836 --> 01:04:00,837
and held rites.

1145
01:04:00,920 --> 01:04:02,797
I had no one to talk to.

1146
01:04:02,881 --> 01:04:06,342
Then one day, I saw a Tagada ride

1147
01:04:06,426 --> 01:04:09,387
and people jumping on it.
I thought it was so cool.

1148
01:04:09,471 --> 01:04:11,890
Others get paid to work as a DJ,

1149
01:04:11,973 --> 01:04:13,558
but I paid to be one.

1150
01:04:15,060 --> 01:04:17,395
So…

1151
01:04:17,479 --> 01:04:18,772
I jump around a lot during rites.

1152
01:04:20,440 --> 01:04:22,609
And on a Tagada.

1153
01:04:26,362 --> 01:04:28,698
It's my only hobby.

1154
01:04:28,782 --> 01:04:30,617
It's how I relieve stress.

1155
01:04:31,493 --> 01:04:33,244
I may be a shaman,

1156
01:04:34,829 --> 01:04:37,874
but I also want to live
as 18-year-old Park Junpyo.

1157
01:04:37,957 --> 01:04:40,126
I thought the deities
would allow that much,

1158
01:04:40,210 --> 01:04:41,711
so I got their permission.

1159
01:04:41,795 --> 01:04:43,671
We need to help him not get sick.

1160
01:04:43,755 --> 01:04:45,215
I wanted to cheer him up.

1161
01:04:45,882 --> 01:04:47,467
So I took him to the Tagada.

1162
01:04:48,718 --> 01:04:50,178
So he could blow off some steam.

1163
01:04:50,261 --> 01:04:51,721
With their permission,

1164
01:04:51,805 --> 01:04:54,891
I was able to enjoy myself
as Park Junpyo the teenage boy.

1165
01:04:54,974 --> 01:04:58,103
In that moment,
I'm not Young Master Jiseon the shaman.

1166
01:04:58,186 --> 01:04:59,479
I feel like myself.

1167
01:05:01,523 --> 01:05:03,358
He sure is something.

1168
01:05:03,441 --> 01:05:06,569
Over there,
people think I'm a Tagada Disco DJ.

1169
01:05:08,488 --> 01:05:10,698
I only have 2 real friends

1170
01:05:10,782 --> 01:05:12,575
who know that I'm a shaman.

1171
01:05:12,659 --> 01:05:14,494
We have no friends.

1172
01:05:14,577 --> 01:05:16,538
We have no common ground.

1173
01:05:17,455 --> 01:05:20,041
I have a job where I talk to people

1174
01:05:20,125 --> 01:05:22,961
like I'm old enough
to be my friends' parents,

1175
01:05:23,044 --> 01:05:24,712
grandparents, or aunts.

1176
01:05:24,796 --> 01:05:27,006
I don't really know
how to talk to people my age.

1177
01:05:29,259 --> 01:05:30,885
Hmm…

1178
01:05:31,344 --> 01:05:34,430
Why are our concerns so similar?

1179
01:05:35,140 --> 01:05:36,141
I know, right?

1180
01:05:37,600 --> 01:05:39,185
Buddha said

1181
01:05:39,811 --> 01:05:41,229
humans are born to be lonely.

1182
01:05:41,312 --> 01:05:43,273
We are born lonely.

1183
01:05:43,815 --> 01:05:46,734
Family, children, friends.

1184
01:05:46,818 --> 01:05:48,945
You can't take them with you when you die.

1185
01:05:49,028 --> 01:05:51,072
Maybe the deities will gather you up.

1186
01:05:51,781 --> 01:05:52,907
That's it.

1187
01:05:53,950 --> 01:05:55,285
Everyone's lonely.

1188
01:05:56,452 --> 01:05:59,038
You need to give up on some things.

1189
01:05:59,122 --> 01:06:02,667
That's our fate,
so I recommend you accept it.

1190
01:06:02,750 --> 01:06:04,627
If you have 2 good friends,

1191
01:06:05,378 --> 01:06:07,714
you can get by just fine with them.

1192
01:06:08,256 --> 01:06:10,258
- I agree with that.
- That's great life advice.

1193
01:06:10,341 --> 01:06:11,426
Thank you.

1194
01:06:11,509 --> 01:06:12,510
Keep your chin up.

1195
01:06:17,932 --> 01:06:20,101
Fate Reapers.

1196
01:06:20,727 --> 01:06:22,187
Between Young Master Jiseon

1197
01:06:22,270 --> 01:06:23,771
and Noh Seulbi,

1198
01:06:23,855 --> 01:06:26,232
choose the survivor.

1199
01:06:26,774 --> 01:06:28,234
This is driving me insane.

1200
01:06:28,318 --> 01:06:30,528
Who matched them up?

1201
01:06:30,612 --> 01:06:33,198
- They did. They chose each other.
- Oh, right.

1202
01:06:33,281 --> 01:06:34,282
For God's sake.

1203
01:06:34,782 --> 01:06:36,326
The Battle of Qi.

1204
01:06:39,120 --> 01:06:41,456
The winner of the 1-on-1 face-off is…

1205
01:06:48,463 --> 01:06:49,797
I can't watch.

1206
01:07:55,280 --> 01:07:57,282
Translated by Jennifer Jean Lim
